records.title: Key 0000
records.name: Key 0 (Master key)
records.look_text: It used to open every door in Tibia. However, that is not the case anymore. Shapeshifter was the owner of this key and many other unique keys. Since Shapeshifter was hacked, his key collection (including key 0000) was lost. Other collectors have tracked down the hacker and bought the key collection to preserve its history and did so successfully. This key was added into the game by one of the map creators (before CipSoft became a big company they used volunteers to do areas). This person added the key into the game in secret. When CipSoft found out that there was a hidden key, they removed its function. The old master key was wooden (brown) and the new one is magical (purple).

records.title: Key 3667
records.name: Key 3667 (Lost Devil Helmet Quest Key)
records.look_text: This key can be found in a dead body in a cave behind Mad Mage Quest room. There's a rope spot west from chests where you get the rewards. Go up, then south. Go down to a room with three Cyclops and down again to a small cave with some Rats. The corpse is located in the south-east corner under some rubbish. This key opens the door to a room, over the Minotaur Outcasts' camp, where Cyclops guard Key 3610 and some other treasures. There's a Lever that allows access to the same room by moving part of the wall but it also closes the way back and can only be used once every Floor Reset. Key 3610 is needed for the Devil Helmet Quest which is a level 30 quest but you need to get past level 40 Gate of Expertise to get key 3667.

records.title: Key 4023
records.name: Key 4023
records.look_text: Opens the door to the Desert Dungeon Teleport Room. You will receive this key when you take Adrenius' quiz for 500 gold pieces. Say the following: {{Infobox Transcript| ''Player'': '''Netlios''' Adrenius: This fool! His book is nothing but a hoax! At least I believe that. Or did you find an answer for my questions? ''Player'': '''yes''' Adrenius: By the way, I would like a donation for my temple. Are 500 gold ok? ''Player'': '''yes''' Adrenius: Thank you very much. Now, name me the first person in alphabetical order, his age, his fate, and how long he was on his journeys! ''Player'': '''anaso, 41, attacked by mother-bear, 117 days''' Adrenius: Hmmm, maybe. What can you tell me about the second 'adventurer'? ''Player'': '''elaeus, 39, attacked by dragon, 100 days''' Adrenius: Yes, that might be true. What did you find out about the third man? ''Player'': '''gadinius, 42, stepped in fire, 83 days''' Adrenius: Correct again! Hmmmm... I doubt you know anything about the fourth person! ''Player'': '''heso, 40, attacked by troll, 66 days''' Adrenius: Yes! Really, how did you figure that out? I bet, you don't know anything about the last adventurer! ''Player'': '''hestus, 38, drank poison, 134 days''' Adrenius: That's right! Why didn't I see it? It's obvious, Netlios was right, and his stories are great! Wait, I'll give you something! }}

records.title: Key 4037
records.name: Key 4037
records.look_text: Opens the door to the Hall of Lost Doors. The book containing the recipe for the potion of regained vision is in one of the bookcases in the library. To receive a key from Nemal you must have all ingredients listed in the recipe. {{Infobox Transcript| ''Player'': '''blind''' Nemal: Yes, I seem to be blind. But I am not sure - maybe the dungeons are too dark! ''Player'': '''potion of regained vision''' Nemal: I heard of a potion of regained vision ... but I can't remember how to make it! Maybe you can help me. Do you know something about it? ''Player'': '''yes''' Nemal: So, did you bring the ingredients with you, stranger? ''Player'': '''yes''' Nemal: You seem to have them with you. Can you tell me, how many minutes I have to cook them? ''Player'': '''31''' Nemal: Ah. It seems to work. But what are the words I have to speak? ''Player'': '''nalus murtu''' Nemal: Thank you! NALUS MURTUUU! ... I can see again! To show you, how grateful I am, I'll give you a key. Be wise when using it. I can't tell you, where it matches, but ... take good care, it is useless without mental powers! }}

records.title: Key 3100

It was the same questions as nowadays in the Noble Armor Quest with the difference that if you answered wrong you would find yourself in the temple while he said something about being unworthy. There are only a few copies of this rare key left on Antica and a unique one on Nova that was obtained by Erana from a game at a Tibia Convention.
